@comment  node-name, next,      previous,  up
@chapter Filesystems support

Currently, wipefreespace does the following actions on supported filesystems:

@enumerate

@item Ext2/3/4 (native, working libraries from e2fsprogs):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks
@item wiping deleted files' data (part of free space or partially used blocks),
wiping deleted files' names and setting deleted files' names' lengths once to zero
@item wiping the journal
@end itemize

@item NTFS (libntfs: not official - not written by the filesystem's creators, written without
any specifications)
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks
@item wiping deleted files' names, deleted files' names' lengths (wiping, not zeroing once),
wiping deleted files' data (part of free space or partially used blocks)
@item wiping the journal
@end itemize

@item XFS (only supported by executing xfs_db from xfsprogs, because I haven't found any
usable development library):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping undelete data (actually does nothing, because XFS doesn't have undelete capability)
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks
@end itemize

@item ReiserFSv3 (using the library from reiserfsprogs, but that library is not a
part of any official development package):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks, but only if the block has just 1 item
@item wiping deleted files' names
@item wiping the journal
@end itemize

@item ReiserFSv4 (using the library from reiser4progs-devel):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item @strong{NOT} wiping free space in partially used blocks (because blocks can be shared
by more than 1 object)
@item @strong{NOT} wiping deleted files' names (but the filesystem itself seems to do it)
@item wiping the journal
@end itemize

@item FAT12/16/32 (using the library from tffs-lib):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks
@item wiping deleted files' names
@end itemize

@item MinixFS (using the mfstool program as a library):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks
@item wiping deleted files' names
@end itemize

@item JFS (using the library from jfsuitls):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping the journal (log)
@end itemize

@item HFS+ (using the library from hfsplus):
@itemize
@item wiping the free space
@item wiping free space in partially used blocks
@end itemize

@end enumerate

